## Risk Assessment

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|------------|--------|------------|
| Fixing auth bypass breaks local dev workflows | Medium | Medium | Provide `make dev` or `.env.dev` that explicitly opts into unsafe mode |
| Deleting `validator_keys.json` breaks dev scripts | Low | Medium | Replace with generated fixture; update scripts to call generator |
| B023 fix changes blockchain behavior unexpectedly | Low | High | Add multi-chain integration test before fix; review diff carefully |
| Mypy baseline hides real bugs | Medium | Medium | Baseline is temporary; sprint to shrink exclusions each release |
| CI tool consolidation breaks existing workflows | Medium | Low | Test new install path in a feature branch first |
| Moving `mutants/` breaks mutation-test reporting | Low | Low | Update CI artifact upload path; verify dashboard links |
| Disabling docs in production breaks API consumers | Low | Medium | Announce change; provide static OpenAPI JSON export as replacement |
| Removing default secrets breaks unconfigured dev environments | Medium | Low | Add `scripts/setup_dev_secrets.py` that generates random local secrets |
| Module split breaks existing imports | Medium | Medium | Keep re-export aliases in old modules during deprecation window |

---

## Dependencies and Prerequisites
- Python 3.13.5 (locked)
- `trufflehog` or `detect-secrets` for secret scanning
- `pytest-cov` if keeping coverage in `addopts`, otherwise remove it

